OL,3,CWhat you need to know as party leaders
OL,4,Cset to go head-to-head in live debate
OL,6,FInstead of each constituency being
OL,7,Frepresented by one person who wins
OL,8,Fwith a straight majority, each of
OL,9,Fthose constituencies will have six
OL,10,Fmembers who could be from different
OL,11,Fparties or independent candidates.
OL,13,FThe constituencies are different.
OL,14,FThere are 16 and they are much larger.
OL,15,FThey're based on the boundaries of two
OL,16,FWestminster constituencies and with
OL,17,Fsingle Welsh-only names such as
OL,18,FCaerdydd Ffynon Taf or Fflint Wrecsam.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
